actical orientation, the work considers the social forms, functions, and rhetorical strategies of the present-day communication of the Gospel and also presents a variety of innovative interpretative approaches.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCommunicationxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aEvangelistic work. 0aMissions. 0aTheology, Practical. 4aKommunikation des Evangeliums. 4aPraktische Theologie. 7aRELIGION / Christian Life / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE,RELIGIONSWISS., JUDAISTIK  2012z9783110288957oZDB-23-DGF40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311022112140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110221121423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110221121/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2012  aZDB-23-DGGb2012  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014